+# Multi-Model Routing (Paperclip ⇄ HQ Commander Doctrine)
+
+Branch: `feat/multi-model-routing`
+Status: Built 2026-05-08. Tests pass. Not merged. Soak alongside Paperclip watchdog.
+
+---
+
+## What this is
+
+A typed translation of HQ Commander's `~/claude-hq/commander/MODEL_ROUTING.md`
+doctrine into Paperclip's heartbeat dispatch path. Every Paperclip agent
+heartbeat now has its `config.model` *checked* — and possibly *adjusted* — by
+the doctrine before the adapter is invoked.
+
+The change is one insertion in `server/src/services/heartbeat.ts` plus a
+new `server/src/services/modelRouting/` module.
+
+## Why it exists
+
+The 2026-04-28 quota incident: three Paperclip agents (Validator, Builder,
+Planner) were configured on Opus 4.7 by default. Their heartbeats burned
+~66M tokens in 30 minutes overnight, depleting 91 percent of the daily
+Anthropic Max-plan quota. After the incident, agents were *manually*
+patched to Sonnet 4.5.
+
+This branch automates that decision: Paperclip now routes each agent to a
+tier-appropriate model based on the agent's role/name. Validator → Haiku,
+Builder → Sonnet, Researcher → Opus, anything containing "reviewer" or
+"architect" → Opus (hard floor, refuses downgrade).
+
+## Where it lives
+
+```
+server/src/services/modelRouting/
+├── doctrine.ts        # data + types: Tier, hard-floor list, keyword → tier table
+├── router.ts          # routeModel() pure function, the decision algorithm
+└── router.test.ts     # 18 vitest tests, all passing
+```
+
+Insertion site: `server/src/services/heartbeat.ts` after
+`applyRunScopedMentionedSkillKeys` builds `effectiveResolvedConfig`.
+
+## How the decision is made
+
+```
+1. HQ_ROUTER_OFF=1                  → passthrough (model unchanged)
+2. Pick a candidate tier:
+     a. HQ_MODEL_OVERRIDE=<tier>    → that tier
+     b. Doctrine keyword match      → tier from KEYWORD_TIER_TABLE in doctrine.ts
+     c. Default                     → sonnet
+3. Hard floor (HARD_FLOOR_PATTERNS) → forces opus, beats step 2
+4. HQ_MODEL_FLOOR=<tier>            → never go below this (raises only)
+```
+
+The router never throws. If anything is malformed, it returns sonnet.
+
+## Disabling — three options
+
+| Want | Set this env var |
+|---|---|
+| Disable routing entirely (back to upstream Paperclip behaviour) | `HQ_ROUTER_OFF=1` |
+| Force one tier for the whole session | `HQ_MODEL_OVERRIDE=opus` (or sonnet/haiku) |
+| Never go below a tier | `HQ_MODEL_FLOOR=sonnet` |
+
+These are read from `process.env` at every dispatch — no restart needed.
+
+## What this branch does NOT touch
+
+- Adapter internals — adapters that ignore `config.model` (plain webhook adapters) are unaffected.
+- Per-agent `config.model` defaults — those remain the operator's control. The router *overlays* on top.
+- Database schema — no migrations in this branch. Cost-ledger column extensions (`override_reason`, `matched_keyword`) are a follow-up.
+- Cross-provider routing (Phase 2 in HQ Commander's doctrine) — Paperclip stays Anthropic-only here.
+- Quality-gate sampling (Phase 3) — deferred.
+- Quota-aware degradation (Phase 4) — deferred.
+
+## How to revert
+
+```bash
+git switch master
+git branch -D feat/multi-model-routing   # only if you're sure
+```
+
+The current `master` branch is untouched and tracks `paperclipai/paperclip`
+upstream — which is read-only to us. Reverting cannot lose data.
+
+## Tests
+
+```bash
+cd server
+pnpm exec vitest run src/services/modelRouting/router.test.ts
+```
+
+18 tests cover: defaults, doctrine matches, hard floor, env overrides,
+override + floor interaction, robustness against null inputs.
+
+## Telemetry
+
+Every routing decision is logged via the existing pino logger:
+
+- **Model changed** — `logger.info` with `modelRouting.applied`, includes the previous model, routed model, tier, override reason, and matched keyword.
+- **Model unchanged** — `logger.debug` with `modelRouting.unchanged`, same fields. Quiet by default.
+
+A future patch can wire these into Paperclip's `cost_events` table by
+extending the schema; this branch deliberately keeps the DB schema clean.
+
+## Observability
+
+If you want to see routing in action without running the full Paperclip
+server, the function is pure and pure-testable:
+
+```ts
+import { routeModel } from "./modelRouting/router.js";
+
+const decision = routeModel({
+  agentKind: "Validator",
+  currentModel: "claude-opus-4-7",
+  env: process.env,
+});
+// → { model: "claude-haiku-4-5-...", tier: "haiku", overrideReason: "doctrine_match", matchedKeyword: "validator", passthrough: false }
+```
+
+## Reference
+
+- Authoritative doctrine: `~/claude-hq/commander/MODEL_ROUTING.md`
+- Quota incident memory: `~/.claude/projects/-Users-sunil-rajput/memory/project_quota_incident_2026_04_28.md`
+- Sister system (PATS dedicated watchdog): `~/claude-hq/watchdogs/pats/`
+- Paperclip dedicated watchdog (built same day): `~/claude-hq/watchdogs/paperclip/`
